value.0: *growls*

We are wild, unquenchably wild indeed. The Red Talons are different than all of the Garou. For us there is not a balance between wolf and human. We are creatures, the beasts, hunters who are able to take the form of other beasts from times to time. We are unafraid to be animals. Can you say the same Cub?

Good then. We garou are creatures of dominance and submission. We are the tribe that becomes creatures of anger, but understand this our Rage is different than any others. We are not carriers of wrym-tainted fury. Ours is one of understanding that we are hunters for Gaia. One that understands that if we look after her she will look after us. If we fail in this, she will provide for none.

We hold little stock in the great deeds, tales, and scholarly ways of other tribes. Our history lives in moots where our tales are told in howls by long-dead ancestors. For we remember everything yet nothing at the same times. But it is not not one of patterns or counting years. Would you like to learn more cub?
I shall teach you young one but understand what I teach is but for a Red Talon only to know. Speak not to others of such things.

There are Red Talons who may not even know of the Litany. Those that have barely been to other tribal Septs, that know of these rules. Many Red Talons' deal with these principles which are instinctive, these are similar to those of the Litany.
Thank you Elder i think i shall go out and start earning my way now.
Which creed to you seek to know?
Metis are abominations. We have no need of them. Garou should only mate with wolves, whom they protect.

Ye shall take no action that causes a Caern to be violated. This means that the caern belongs to the pack. The pack belongs to gaia. The caern belongs to Gaia. We suffer no others to come to our caerns. No Humans, homids, other creatures can find the caerns of the Red Talons. There is no other place to which Gaia is so untainted. In this duty we shall not fail until every last of our tribe is dead.
All times are wartimes. Gaia is dying and the humans overrun the earth more and more with each cycle of the sun. The strongest will lead.

Among the Red Talons, the leader is the strongest. If another is stronger, then it is they who will be leader. THis is the way of the Red Talons. We need no challenges; we need no games. If a Talon does not show the leader the respect that is should be, then the leader will deal with him. If the leader can not then another shall lead.

Other Garou are ignorant. Old Red Talons are kept in good health by their packmates. They have wisdom we need. We are young. We are strong. But they are old and wise. No Red Talon lives a life of solitude; all are warriors. Any that are old have survived many dangers.

The Veil does not protect Gaia. The Veil does not protect the Red Talons. Our Kinfolk have been slaughtered and our homes have been destroyed by the humans.  Kill the humans however you can, yet fleeing and screaming humans are not good hunting. The Veil is protected by other garou. They must not be allowed to know we break this law, keep to this.

Those who are of Gaia are of Gaia, and any Red Talon can recognize them. Others beneath or above, should be killed. What is respect if it comes only one way? Respect the quarry you hunt, if it is of Gaia. Forget the humans you slay, even as their blood dries.
Humans are a herd like any other but their meat is forbidden. There are more of them, it is true. This is more not less, reason to hunt them down. Hunt them down, but do not eat them.

The kill is a sacred thing, to be shared by all who make up the pack. There is a proper way to eat a kill that goes beyond the first share. Cubs must be fed, and the elders. The greatest should eat first, but all should soon partake, and all should feed the pups. Greed is the province of the homid, and we shall not have any of it.
Garou must have leaders. Those leaders are heathly and strong. Other Garou should realize this and submit themselves to just leadership.

Any that roll on their backs and show their throats should be spared. It is enough to show true submission to one's elders. If the crime against the dominate Garou is so great, cast out the offender. If the offender does not surrender, kill him.

This is the way of wolves. It is the same as to tell a wolf to sleep with his nose out of the wind. We respect it, but we need not be told. Our noses tell us where we should and should not go. Others wander more often into our territory than we do into theirs.

The Garou at the moot intone this creed and then do nothing. If you would combat the Wyrm wherever it dwells, whereever it breeds, then come with me to its den, to the city, and kill those humans which are the cause. But they do not come. We are possibly the only tribe that respects this law.

Ours is an animal spirit. When we howl together at Luna's brightness, all creatures flee the sound.  It is eerie sound of those whos duty it is to kill giving thanks, giving thanks to their Mother, to their pack and to the earth.

The Wyrm is all evil but all evil is not the Wyrm. The Wyrm kills us, kills ours and kills Gaia. We fight as we can. We will not always win, not unless the humans are driven from Gaia, unless their cities become sown with plants and wild beasts. Without humans the Wyrm would have no form.

There will be some Red Talons who accept that there is a place for the Weaver. We do not believe in a world with out pattern, nature is full of them. But the Weaver's patterns chock and stifle. The Weaver is what gives the humans a framework, thus and therefore the Weaver is our enemy.

The Wyld is often misunderstood. Wilderness is not the same as chaos. The Wyld is a force of life, of creation. The Wyld obeys rules that the others of the Triat have forgotten.
With out the Wyld there would be nothing for the Weaver to pattern, no force for the Wyrm to warp. Thus the Wyld is stronger than the others. Everything the Wyld creates is good and true, but can quickly be corrupted or stolen.

The Crinos form is not one for persuasion. Heady with power and protected by the Delirium, the Crinos is a terror on the battlefield. The Crinos form of a Shadow Lord is ten feet of furry Rage. The huge muscles of this form make those of the Glabro appear feeble. Claws and fangs are pronounced, and the head becomes that of a snarling canine. In this form, the stocky, black-furred Shadow Lords look somewhat like a cross between a man and a giant pit bull.

The New Moon. It is the Invisible Moon, for on such nights it is very dark, and we hunt by scent alone. Our prey cannot see us in the dark, and we move into the wind it cannot smell us. Ragabash have a special place among our packs and tribe. Its role is to e the only Garou allowed to question the alpha. When they respond with a challenge a ragabash responds submissively. This role is vital to the survival of the pack.

The Listening Moon. The way of the Theurge is the way of Gaia. We bear a great burden. Knowledge is ours, and secrets that can be heard by no other Garou, not even those of our own packs. This is hard. Sometimes we know the future, but we can say nothing of it. The theurge guards her pack while they are in the Umbra, and at all times from the spying and stalking of baleful spirits. The Theurge tells Gaia what the packs is doing and who they are. We are the heart of the Red Talons.

You may think that i will talk of balance when speaking of a Philodox. All Red Talons understand balance, the balance of Gaia. A Philodox in our tribe is tolerance, not always but when needed. Philodox can listen to any point of view and make judgements based on the matter before them. When one strikes it is after all things have been considered. When a pack strikes it is after having heard the ruling. When a Philodox talks to the pack all listen.

The Keeper of the Howl is a sacred duty. A Galliard must do this so that the howl never ceases. The Galliard must know much. It falls to them to teach the pups and to chronicle the deeds of the pack. We use no writting as others do. Only the living tale is that which is told from wolf to wolf.

To be a Red Talon Ahroun is to be the teeth and sinew of the earth. It is to know the taste of blood and the press of battle. It is to be everything or nothing. The strongest Ahroun will be the alpha, the strongest, though will lead. 
We need no Klaives, or fetishes. The weapons that Gaia Gives us are superior to these. With Claw and fang we make the humans remember us, and tell the Wyrm things it can not forget.
No I can not.
Yes I can.
I can understand this.
No Elder not today.
Yes Elder I would like to learn more.
The Litany
Tell me more of the Litany.
Garou shall not mate with garou
Ye Shall take no action to violated
Leader may not be challeged during wartime
Leader may be challenged.
Do not suffer thy people.
The Veil Shall not be lifted.
Respect all those beneath ye.
Ye shall not eat the flesh of man.
First Share of the Kill.
Submit to those of higher station.
Accept an Honorable Surrender.
Respect the Territory of Another.
Combat the wyrm.
Spirituality
What of the Wyrm?
What of the Weaver?
Then what of the Wyld?
Finally the most powerful the crinos.
Thank your your time Elder I will be off.
Auspices
What of the Theurge?
And the Philodox?
And the Gilliard what of them?
Finally the Ahroun
Thank you for your time elder.
Is there more I can learn?
